I've watched every AI wave since the first chatbots.

@clickup 's Brain² is the first one that does not make me pick a model or start over each session. 

It already knows my work. https://t.co/IIFtRreGqB

@oliverkenyon @marclou The expected return of indie vs VC I feel is oddly the same, if you're succesful you'll eventually end up at around $50M to $100M net worth

Even billion dollar startups, the founders end up with only ~5% ownership on average, that is if they become successful at all

The difference is that we don't have the stress of managing staff etc

@elonmusk I proposed AI industry regulatory authority at my TED Talk in 2023. 

Good time to rewatch!

https://t.co/1dCPVekIjU

@sobedominik Same

I do insane amazing stuff now never possible before for me but I feel less achievement than ever

It feels like being a manager and not a coder

AI doesn't make organizations more agile by default. It just makes them faster, in whichever direction they're already heading.

@PMInstitute's new research digs into why that distinction matters more than ever. 

Here's the breakdown… https://t.co/zh3qmEelFq

